{"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP"],"title":"Conforms To"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ActionGroupRef","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Actions can be used to expose functionality in a structured way, either","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from one part of a program to another, or to the outside world. Action"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"groups are often used together with a [type"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MenuModel","isActive":true},{"text":"] that provides additional","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"representation data for displaying the actions to the user, e.g. in a menu.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The main way to interact with the actions in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GActionGroup"},{"text":" is to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"activate them with [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ActionGroup.activate_action"},{"text":"]. Activating an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"action may require a [type[Variant](\/\/documentation\/glib\/variant] parameter. The required type of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parameter can be inquired with [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ActionGroup.get_action_parameter_type"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Actions may be disabled, see [method"},{"code":"Gio.ActionGroup.get_action_enabled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Activating a disabled action has no effect.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Actions may optionally have a state in the form of a [type[Variant](\/\/documentation\/glib\/variant]. The current","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"state of an action can be inquired with [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ActionGroup.get_action_state"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Activating a stateful action may change its state, but it is also possible to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"set the state by calling [method"},{"code":"Gio.ActionGroup.change_action_state","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As typical example, consider a text editing application which has an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"option to change the current font to ‘bold’. A good way to represent"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this would be a stateful action, with a boolean state. Activating the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"action would toggle the state."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each action in the group has a unique name (which is a string).  All"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"method calls, except [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ActionGroup.list_actions"},{"text":"] take the name of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"an action as an argument."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GActionGroup"},{"text":" API is meant to be the ‘public’ API to the action","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group. The calls here are exactly the interaction that ‘external","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"forces’ (eg: UI, incoming D-Bus messages, etc.) are supposed to have","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with actions. ‘Internal’ APIs (ie: ones meant only to be accessed by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the action group implementation) are found on subclasses. This is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"why you will find – for example – [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ActionGroup.get_action_enabled"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"but not an equivalent "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"set_action_enabled()"},{"text":" method.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Signals are emitted on the action group in response to state changes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on individual actions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Implementations of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GActionGroup"},{"text":" should provide implementations for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the virtual functions [method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.ActionGroup.list_actions","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ActionGroup.query_action"},{"type":"text","text":"]. The other virtual functions should"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not be implemented — their ‘wrappers’ are actually implemented with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calls to [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.ActionGroup.query_action"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GActionGroup"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupProtocol"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GActionGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroup","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GActionGroup"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GActionGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a group of actions."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/actiongroupref"]}],"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(_:)-2bbiw","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(_:)-2rcly","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(_:)-44qs9","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(_:)-7d9","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(_:)-8cyy3","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/ptr"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/ActionGroupProtocol-Implementations","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ActionGroupRef","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ActionGroupRef","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO14ActionGroupRefV","roleHeading":"Structure","symbolKind":"struct","title":"ActionGroupRef","role":"symbol"},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/ActionGroupRef/init(_:)-8cyy3":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GActionGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":">)"}],"title":"init(_:)","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Designated initialiser from the underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"type":"text","text":" data type"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/ActionGroupRef\/init(_:)-8cyy3","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/actiongroupre